data.text: Anyway, Woody is terrible and I regret spending money to support a monster, but Annie Hall and Crimes & Misdemeanors and Hannah & Her Sisters are so good, they make me hope for another. I'm very sorry. But Timberlake is equally appalling

Anyway, Winslet literally acts circles around him at one point. She has a two minute monologue where she smokes and unravels in a very Judy Davis in a Woody Allen movie way, then it cuts to Timberlake and he goes, "Yes."

In the climax of the film, Timby confronts Winslet after she sends the mob after Juno because she's a jealous lady and gets her killed. He's furious with her! "I KNOW WHAT YOU DID!" he accuses her. Timby delivers the line like this: https://t.co/1fw9e0raZL
But his lines are delivered with such a stilted delivery, it's as if this script was written out phonetically and he's just making mouth sounds
Juno Temple (under-served here but excellent in Afternoon Delight, rent that shit) is Belushi's daughter running from the mob. And Justin is supposed to be this brilliant playwright

Kate Winslet is a sad lady and Jim Belushi is her drunk husband. I like to think Woody took a stand on this casting. They suggest someone of Winslet's calibre and he stamped his feel and stammered, "According to Jim! Jesus!"
